<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="389" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,582,789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,582,608]" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">Distribution:</emphasis>
Known only from the Venezuelan and Colombian plains, in the Orinoco River basin (
<bibRefCitation author="Esqueda, L. F." box="[1269,1431,582,609]" pageId="12" pageNumber="389" pagination="33 - 42" refId="ref16263" refString="Esqueda, L. F. (2005) Un nuevo Leposoma (Squamata: Gymnophthalmidae) de la Reserva Forestal de Caparo, estado Barinas, Venezuela. Herpetotropicos, 2 (1), 33 - 42." type="journal article" year="2005">Esqueda 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanchez-Pacheco, S. J. &amp; Rueda-Almonacid, J. V. &amp; Caicedo-Portilla, J. R. &amp; Souza, S. M." box="[151,478,618,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="389" pagination="53 - 57" refId="ref18997" refString="Sanchez-Pacheco, S. J., Rueda-Almonacid, J. V., Caicedo-Portilla, J. R. &amp; Souza, S. M. (2016) First record of Leposoma caparensis from Colombia, with confirmation for the presence of Ptychoglossus myersi and P. plicatus (Squamata: Gymnophthalmidae). Salamandra, 52 (1), 53 - 57." type="journal article" year="2016">
Sánchez-Pacheco 
<emphasis box="[354,410,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[527,637,618,644]" name="Colombia" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">Colombia</collectingCountry>
from the 
<collectingRegion box="[745,959,618,644]" country="Colombia" name="Arauca" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">Arauca department</collectingRegion>
in the northernmost Orinoquia (
<figureCitation box="[1321,1412,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution maps for the cis-Andean microteiid lizards in Colombia (Alopoglossidae + Gymnophthalmidae). Circles are examined specimens, while squares are records from literature (see Supplementary Files for specific references). Red arrows indicate new records for Colombia. Black arrows show a zoom in to regions where several records overlap. The light green shadow indicates the Orinoco River basin, and the dark green the Amazon River basin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5681929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5681929/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,582,789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,385,654,680]" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">Similar species:</emphasis>
Currently, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esqueda" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[508,759,654,680]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="389" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caparensis">
<emphasis box="[508,759,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">Loxopholis caparensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to have an allopatric distribution from other cis-Andean species of the genus. However, it can be differentiated from all the other eastern species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1192,1316,690,716]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="389" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1192,1316,690,716]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">Loxopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry name="Colombia" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">Colombia</collectingCountry>
in having smooth or weakly keeled ventral scales (keeled in 
<emphasis box="[865,1195,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[865,1004,726,752]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="389" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parietalis">L. parietalis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1015,1195,727,752]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="389" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">L. percarinatum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[1256,1419,726,752]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="389" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[1256,1419,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">L. snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and rhomboid dorsal scales (hexagonal in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ayala &amp; Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[624,760,762,788]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="389" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hexalepis">
<emphasis box="[624,760,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="389">L. hexalepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). For a more detailed description see 
<bibRefCitation author="Esqueda, L. F." box="[1182,1362,762,789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="389" pagination="33 - 42" refId="ref16263" refString="Esqueda, L. F. (2005) Un nuevo Leposoma (Squamata: Gymnophthalmidae) de la Reserva Forestal de Caparo, estado Barinas, Venezuela. Herpetotropicos, 2 (1), 33 - 42." type="journal article" year="2005">Esqueda (2005)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
